.nh
.TH g2
Some Gentoo CLI tools I wrote for myself.

.SH Manifest Tools
\fBg2\fR includes a set of tools for working with Gentoo \fBManifest\fR files.

.SS \fBmanifest\fR
The \fBmanifest\fR command group handles operations related to Manifest files.

.SS \fBupsert-from-url\fR
Updates or inserts a \fBManifest\fR entry for a file downloaded from a URL. This command streams the file, calculates the specified checksums, and updates the \fBManifest\fR file in the specified directory (or specific file path).

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 manifest [flags] upsert-from-url <url> <filename> <manifestFileOrDir>
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<url>\fR: The HTTP/HTTPS URL of the file to download.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<filename>\fR: The filename to record in the \fBManifest\fR (typically the distfile name).
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<manifestFileOrDir>\fR: The path to the \fBManifest\fR file or the directory containing it (e.g., the ebuild directory).

.PP
\fBFlags:\fP

.PP
The following flags control which checksums are calculated. Note that \fBBLAKE2B\fR and \fBSHA512\fR are enabled by default.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-blake2b\fR (default: \fBtrue\fR): Calculate BLAKE2B checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-blake2s\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate BLAKE2S checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-md5\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate MD5 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-rmd160\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate RMD160 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha1\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA1 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha256\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA256 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha3_256\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA3-256 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha3_512\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA3-512 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha512\fR (default: \fBtrue\fR): Calculate SHA512 checksum.

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.PP
To download a package, calculate SHA256 in addition to defaults, and update the Manifest in the current directory:

.EX
g2 manifest -sha256=true upsert-from-url https://example.com/software-1.0.tar.gz software-1.0.tar.gz .
.EE

.SH Site Generation
\fBg2\fR can generate a static HTML website representing your Gentoo overlay, including categories, packages, metadata, and git commit history. It also supports aggregating multiple remote overlays.

.SS \fBoverlay site generate\fR
Generates a static site for a single overlay.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 overlay site generate [-out <dir>] [-clear] [<location>]
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<location>\fR: Path to the overlay directory, or a Git URL (defaults to \fB\&.\fR).

.PP
\fBFlags:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-out\fR: Output directory for the generated site (default: \fBsite_out\fR).
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-clear\fR: Clear output directory before generation.

.SS \fBoverlays site generate\fR
Generates an aggregated static site for multiple remote repositories from a \fBrepositories.xml\fR file.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 overlays site generate [-out <dir>] [-clear] <repositoriesFile>
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<repositoriesFile>\fR: Path or URL to a Gentoo \fBrepositories.xml\fR file, or \fB-\fR for stdin.

.SH Linting
\fBg2\fR provides linting to ensure overlay consistency.

.SS \fBlint\fR
Checks the repository for errors such as ebuild \fBIUSE\fR variables missing in \fBmetadata.xml\fR and missing \fBmd5-cache\fR files.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 lint [<location>]
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<location>\fR: Path to the overlay directory (defaults to \fB\&.\fR).

.SH GitHub Action
You can use the g2 GitHub Action
\[la]https://github.com/arran4/g2\-action\[ra] to integrate \fBg2\fR into your CI/CD workflows. It automatically downloads and installs \fBg2\fR for use in your workflow steps.

.SS Example Usage
.EX
name: Example workflow
on: [push]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install g2
        uses: arran4/g2-action@v1
        with:
          # Optional: specify a version. Defaults to 'latest'
          version: 'latest'

      - name: Use g2
        run: |
          g2 lint .

      - name: Use g2 Action
        uses: arran4/g2-action@v1.2
        with:
          # Optional: specify an action
          action: 'lint .'
          # Optional: skip installation if already installed
          mode: 'run'
.EE
